definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  NAD(P)+ + sn-glycerol-1-phosphate -eq- NAD(P)H + H+ + dihydroxy-acetone-phosphate.
Catalysis of the transfer of an alkylthio group from one compound (donor) to another (acceptor).

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on paired donors, with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen, with 2-oxoglutarate as one donor, and the other dehydrogenated

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which hydrogen or electrons are transferred from 2-oxoglutarate and one other donor, and the latter donor is dehydrogenated.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on phosphorus or arsenic in donors, with NAD(P)+ as acceptor

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which a phosphorus- or arsenic-containing group acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces a NAD(P)+ to NAD(P)H.
Catalysis of the reaction -  phosphate + beta-D-galactopyranosyl-(1--gt-3)-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine -eq- N-acetyl-D-glucosamine + alpha-D-galactopyranose 1-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-D-glucuronate + UDP-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine -eq- [beta-N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-(1--gt-4)-beta-D-glucuronosyl-(1--gt-3)](n) + 2n UDP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  cis-zeatin + UDP-D-glucose -eq- O-beta-D-glucosyl-cis-zeatin + H(+) + UDP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  trehalose 6-phosphate + phosphate -eq- glucose 6-phosphate + beta-D-glucose 1-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-phospho-D-glycerate + GDP-alpha-D-mannose -eq- 2-(alpha-D-mannosyl)-3-phosphoglycerate + GDP + H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  hydroquinone + UDP-D-glucose -eq- H(+) + hydroquinone O-beta-D-glucopyranoside + UDP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-D-glucose + vomilenine -eq- H(+) + raucaffricine + UDP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  indoxyl + UDP-D-glucose -eq- H(+) + indican + UDP.

Catalysis of the reaction -  beta-D-glucuronosyl-(1,4)-N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminyl-proteoglycan + UDP-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine -eq- N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminyl-(1,4)-beta-D-glucuronosyl-(1,4)-N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminyl-proteoglycan + UDP.

Catalysis of the reaction -  N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminyl-(1,4)-beta-D-glucuronosyl-proteoglycan + UDP-alpha-D-glucuronate -eq- beta-D-glucuronosyl-(1,4)-N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminyl-(1,4)-beta-D-glucuronosyl-proteoglycan + UDP.

Catalysis of the reaction -  N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1,4)-beta-D-glucuronosyl-proteoglycan + UDP-alpha-D-glucuronate -eq- beta-D-glucuronosyl-(1,3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1,4)-beta-D-glucuronosyl-proteoglycan + UDP.

Catalysis of the reaction -  Mur2Ac(oyl-L-Ala-gamma-D-Glu-L-Lys-D-Ala-D-Ala)-diphosphoundecaprenol + UDP-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine -eq- GlcNAc-(1,4)-Mur2Ac(oyl-L-Ala-gamma-D-Glu-L-Lys-D-Ala-D-Ala)-diphosphoundecaprenol + UDP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  beta-D-galactosyl-(1,4)-D-glucosylceramide + UDP-galactose -eq- alpha-D-galactosyl-(1,4)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1,4)-D-glucosylceramide + UDP.

Catalysis of the reaction -  N(4)-{N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1--gt-2)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1--gt-3)-[N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1--gt-2)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1--gt-6)]-beta-D-mannosyl-(1--gt-4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1--gt-4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl}-L-asparagine + UDP-alpha-D-xylose -eq- N(4)-{N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1--gt-2)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1--gt-3)-[N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1--gt-2)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1--gt-6)]-[beta-D-xylosyl-(1--gt-2)]-beta-D-mannosyl-(1--gt-4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1--gt-4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl}-L-asparagine + H(+) + UDP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  spermidine + putrescine -eq- sym-homospermidine + propane-1,3-diamine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  4-CDP-2-C-methyl-D-erythritol + ATP -eq- 4-CDP-2-C-methyl-D-erythritol 2-phosphate + ADP + 2 H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-C-methyl-D-erythritol 4-phosphate + CTP -eq- 4-CDP-2-C-methyl-D-erythritol + diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  apo-citrate lyase + 2'-(5''-triphosphoribosyl)-3'-dephospho-CoA -eq- diphosphate + holo-citrate lyase.
Catalysis of the reaction -  CDP-diacylglycerol + choline -eq- 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine + CMP + H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + alpha-glucan + H2O -eq- AMP + phospho-alpha-glucan + phosphate.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on phosphorus or arsenic in donors, with other known acceptors

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which phosphorus or arsenic acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces a known acceptor other than disulfide, NAD or NADP.

Catalysis of the reaction -  coenzyme B + methyl-coenzyme M -eq- coenzyme M-coenzyme B heterodisulfide + methane. Methyl-CoM is also known as 2-(methylthio)ethanesulfonate, coenzyme B as N-(7-mercaptoheptanoyl)threonine 3-O-phosphate, and coenzyme M-coenzyme B heterodisulfide as CoM-S-S-CoB.
Catalysis of the reaction -  cutin + H2O -eq- cutin monomers.
Catalysis of the reaction -  H2O + poly[(R)-3-hydroxybutanoate](n) -eq- poly[(R)-3-hydroxybutanoate](x) + poly[(R)-3-hydroxybutanoate](n-x) -  x is 1-5.
Catalysis of the reaction -  H2O + poly[(R)-3-hydroxyoctanoate](n) -eq- poly[(R)-3-hydroxyoctanoate](x) + poly[(R)-3-hydroxyoctanoate](n-x) -  x is 1-5.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-(acyloxy)acyl group of bacterial toxin -eq- 3-hydroxyacyl group of bacterial toxin + a fatty acid.
Catalysis of the reaction -  H(2)O + polyneuridine aldehyde -eq- 16-epivellosimine + CO(2) + methanol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-O-(beta-D-glucosyl)-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate + H(2)O -eq- 2-O-(beta-D-glucosyl)-sn-glycerol + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-(alpha-D-mannosyl)-3-phosphoglycerate + H(2)O -eq- 2-(alpha-D-mannosyl)-D-glycerate + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (2R)-O-phospho-3-sulfolactate + H(2)O -eq- (R)-3-sulfolactate + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  H2O + myo-inositol hexakisphosphate -eq- phosphate + 1L-myo-inositol 1,2,3,4,6-pentakisphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-deoxyoctulosonyl-lipopolysaccharide + H2O -eq- 3-deoxyoctulosonic acid + lipopolysaccharide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  a 6-O-(beta-D-xylopyranosyl)-beta-D-glucopyranoside + H2O -eq- 6-O-(beta-D-xylopyranosyl)-beta-D-glucopyranose + an alcohol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N-acetylphenylethylamine + H(2)O -eq- acetate + phenylethylamine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (R)-mandelamide + H(2)O -eq- (R)-mandelate + NH(4)(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  N-carbamoyl-L-2-amino acid + H2O -eq- L-2-amino acid + NH3 + CO2. The N-carbamoyl-L-2-amino acid is a 2-ureido carboxylate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  H(2)O + maleimide -eq- H(+) + maleamate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-aminomuconate + H(2)O + H(+) -eq- (Z)-5-oxohex-2-enedioate + NH(4)(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  beta-carotene + O2 -eq- beta-apo-10'-carotenal + beta-ionone.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with icosanoids, any C20 polyunsaturated fatty acids or their derivatives, including the leukotrienes and the prostanoids.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with icosatetraenoic acid, any straight-chain fatty acid with twenty carbon atoms and four double bonds per molecule.

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with arachidonic acid, a straight chain fatty acid with 20 carbon atoms and four double bonds per molecule. Arachidonic acid is the all-Z-(5,8,11,14)-isomer.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-sulfopyruvate + H(+) -eq- CO(2) + sulfoacetaldehyde.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (4-hydroxyphenyl)pyruvate + H(+) -eq- (4-hydroxyphenyl)acetaldehyde + CO(2).
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-hydroxy-3-(4-hydroxy-3-methoxyphenyl)propanoyl-CoA -eq- acetyl-CoA + vanillin.
Catalysis of the reaction -  trans-feruloyl-CoA + H2O -eq- 4-hydroxy-3-methoxyphenyl-beta-hydroxypropionyl-CoA.
